  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Distress of Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3359
          },
          {
            "text": "the gold has become tarnished,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the pure gold has become dull!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The gems of the temple lie scattered",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on every street corner.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How the precious sons of Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "once worth their weight in pure gold,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "are now esteemed as jars of clay,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the work of a potter’s hands!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Even jackals",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3360
          },
          {
            "text": "offer their breasts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to nurse their young,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but the daughter of my people has become cruel,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like an ostrich in the wilderness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The nursing infant’s tongue",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "clings in thirst to the roof of his mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Little children beg for bread,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but no one gives them any.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Those who once ate delicacies",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are destitute in the streets;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "those brought up in crimson",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "huddle in ash heaps.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The punishment",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3361
          },
          {
            "text": "of the daughter of my people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is greater than that of Sodom,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "which was overthrown in an instant",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "without a hand turned to help her.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Her dignitaries were brighter than snow,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whiter than milk;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "their bodies were more ruddy than rubies,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their appearance",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3362
          },
          {
            "text": "like sapphires.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3363
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But now their appearance is blacker than soot;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they are not recognized in the streets.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Their skin has shriveled on their bones;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it has become as dry as a stick.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Those slain by the sword are better off",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than those who die of hunger,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who waste away, pierced with pain",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because the fields lack produce.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The hands of compassionate women",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "have cooked their own children,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who became their food",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the destruction of the daughter of my people.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD has exhausted His wrath;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has poured out His fierce anger;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He has kindled a fire in Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and it has consumed her foundations.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The kings of the earth did not believe,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor any people of the world,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that an enemy or a foe",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "could enter the gates of Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But this was for the sins of her prophets",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the guilt of her priests,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who shed the blood of the righteous",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in her midst.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They wandered blind in the streets,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "defiled by this blood,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "so that no one dared",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to touch their garments.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Go away! Unclean!”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "men shouted at them.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Away, away! Do not touch us!”",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "So they fled and wandered.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Among the nations it was said,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“They can stay here no longer.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The presence of the LORD has scattered them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He regards them no more.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The priests are shown no honor;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the elders find no favor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All the while our eyes were failing",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as we looked in vain for help.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "We watched from our towers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for a nation that could not save us.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They stalked our every step,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that we could not walk in our streets.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Our end drew near, our time ran out,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for our end had come!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Those who chased us were swifter",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than the eagles in the sky;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "they pursued us over the mountains",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and ambushed us in the wilderness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD’s anointed, the breath of our life,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "was captured in their pits.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "We had said of him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Under his shadow we will live among the nations.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "So rejoice and be glad, O Daughter of Edom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you who dwell in the land of Uz.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet the cup will pass to you as well;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will get drunk and expose yourself.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O Daughter of Zion, your punishment is complete;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will not prolong your exile.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3364
          },
          {
            "text": "But He will punish your iniquity, O Daughter of Edom;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will expose your sins.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
